[Guest]: up.

01:03:44.240 --> 01:03:50.000
[Guest]: They'd have, you know, half their faces, you know, with blue marks and whatnot.

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:52.840
[Guest]: I was so I just started recognizing.

01:03:52.840 --> 01:03:58.360
[Guest]: So I've had this really bizarre incidents in NID Kurukshetra where, you know, I'll tell

01:03:58.360 --> 01:03:59.360
[Guest]: you a funny one.

01:03:59.360 --> 01:04:03.920
[Guest]: And, you know, it'll also give context to some of the conversations that, you know,

01:04:03.920 --> 01:04:05.880
[Guest]: we're having on gender.

01:04:05.880 --> 01:04:08.480
[Guest]: The first and this is a true story, okay.

01:04:08.480 --> 01:04:16.440
[Guest]: The first day I was in a classroom in NID Kurukshetra and people were asking where all

01:04:16.440 --> 01:04:19.800
[Guest]: teachers would ask you, tell your roll number, where you from, etc, etc.

01:04:19.800 --> 01:04:28.120
[Guest]: So I said, like, you know, whatever roll number 20, 25 and I was from Bahrain and somebody

01:04:28.120 --> 01:04:31.760
[Guest]: said little later, a girl said they're from Dubai.

01:04:31.760 --> 01:04:32.760
[Guest]: I said, oh, cool.

01:04:32.760 --> 01:04:34.920
[Guest]: So after the class, I went to the girl, I said, you're from Dubai, I'm from Bahrain,

01:04:34.920 --> 01:04:37.240
[Guest]: we should like, you know, exchange numbers or whatnot, right?

01:04:37.240 --> 01:04:40.760
[Guest]: She was sitting next to a girl, you know, who was from Faridabad.

01:04:40.760 --> 01:04:41.760
[Guest]: And I said, where are you from?

01:04:41.760 --> 01:04:42.760
[Guest]: She said, I'm from Faridabad.

01:04:42.760 --> 01:04:43.760
[Guest]: I said, great.

01:04:43.760 --> 01:04:47.040
[Guest]: So can we have like, can I have your number also, we'll just keep in touch.

01:04:47.040 --> 01:04:49.880
[Guest]: And now she gave the number, but I thought that she was a little hesitant.

01:04:49.880 --> 01:04:55.280
[Guest]: Now in my head, you know, like, in Bahrain, all the boys and girls, we all used to talk,

01:04:55.280 --> 01:05:00.240
[Guest]: there was never like a whole thing, which I never realized that NID is like a big thing

01:05:00.240 --> 01:05:04.080
[Guest]: for a guy to ask a girl a number and like, take it and whatnot.

01:05:04.080 --> 01:05:06.080
[Guest]: I didn't realize all of this, okay?

01:05:06.080 --> 01:05:08.760
[Guest]: At night, I have to go, I'm in my room.

01:05:08.760 --> 01:05:09.760
[Guest]: And there's a knock.

01:05:09.760 --> 01:05:13.760
[Guest]: We used to live it to first year, live it to roommates, there's a knock on my door.

01:05:13.760 --> 01:05:21.080
[Guest]: I open the door and there's this big Haryanvi Jat guy, you know, with his four or five other

01:05:21.080 --> 01:05:24.200
[Guest]: all well built, strong, good looking folks.

01:05:24.200 --> 01:05:27.960
[Guest]: And then he just aggressively asked me, look, what do you think he is?

01:05:27.960 --> 01:05:31.440
[Guest]: I'm like, who are you?

01:05:31.440 --> 01:05:32.440
[Guest]: What happened?

01:05:32.440 --> 01:05:33.440
[Guest]: I'd never seen him before.

01:05:33.440 --> 01:05:34.440
[Guest]: Maybe I've seen him before, but I don't know his context.

01:05:34.440 --> 01:05:37.000
[Guest]: He's like, do you think he's Bond?

01:05:37.000 --> 01:05:42.360
[Guest]: I'm just like Bond, I'm thinking chemistry, covalent bond, you know, I'm like Bond?

01:05:42.360 --> 01:05:44.360
[Guest]: And he's like, do you think you're James Bond?

01:05:44.360 --> 01:05:47.760
[Guest]: I was like, no, bro, what are you talking about?

01:05:47.760 --> 01:05:50.080
[Guest]: He's like, will you take a girl's number?

01:05:50.080 --> 01:05:54.120
[Guest]: And I'm just like, first of all, I didn't even recognize, he's like, how did you take

01:05:54.120 --> 01:05:55.120
[Guest]: her number?

01:05:55.120 --> 01:05:56.120
[Guest]: I was like, okay, what happened?

01:05:56.120 --> 01:06:02.080
[Guest]: He's like, do you know that the girl from Faridabad, one of the guys said the girl from

01:06:02.080 --> 01:06:03.600
[Guest]: Faridabad is his girlfriend.

01:06:03.600 --> 01:06:04.600
[Guest]: Do you know that?

01:06:04.600 --> 01:06:06.720
[Guest]: I was like, I had no clue, you know, how would I know?

01:06:06.720 --> 01:06:10.920
[Guest]: And I'm okay, delete the number, man, I was just being friendly, I'm not like pursuing

01:06:10.920 --> 01:06:12.160
[Guest]: her or whatever.

01:06:12.160 --> 01:06:16.760
[Guest]: So he's like, delete number, delete the number, delete it, you know, he's like, don't you

01:06:16.760 --> 01:06:19.760
[Guest]: don't mess with the girl from Faridabad, I'll come and beat you up.

01:06:19.760 --> 01:06:20.760
[Guest]: That was his whole thing.

01:06:20.760 --> 01:06:24.280
[Guest]: And all these guys gave me like, this is your last first and last warning, you know, and

01:06:24.280 --> 01:06:25.840
[Guest]: I was like, dude, sorry.

01:06:25.840 --> 01:06:30.400
[Guest]: And I was like, I'm a coward, no, I'm from Bahrain, I have a whole cushioned life, suddenly

01:06:30.400 --> 01:06:31.400
[Guest]: in Bahrain, etc, etc.

01:06:31.400 --> 01:06:36.200
[Guest]: I was a big fat kid, you know, who also wore these loose clothes, I was like fully like,

01:06:36.200 --> 01:06:37.200
[Guest]: what's happening to me?

01:06:37.200 --> 01:06:41.480
[Guest]: So I said, sorry, sorry, please delete the number, I'm not a hero, please go away.

01:06:41.480 --> 01:06:43.360
[Guest]: So he went away.

01:06:43.360 --> 01:06:45.840
[Guest]: And then sometime and I was just like, my roommates were like, my roommates were also

01:06:45.840 --> 01:06:46.840
[Guest]: from the Middle East.

01:06:46.840 --> 01:06:50.280
[Guest]: So we kind of had figured out, okay, let's live together.

01:06:50.280 --> 01:06:55.040
[Guest]: And they were also looking at me like, you know, do you not realize that, you know, in

01:06:55.040 --> 01:06:59.080
[Guest]: this place, etc, etc, you can't be so open with girls, you know, people like, you have

01:06:59.080 --> 01:07:02.360
[Guest]: to be really smart about it, I was like, okay, I'll try and be like really smart about it.

01:07:02.360 --> 01:07:04.640
[Guest]: And then sometime later, this guy comes back.

01:07:04.640 --> 01:07:05.640
[Guest]: And this time he's alone.

01:07:05.640 --> 01:07:10.760
[Guest]: So I was like, bro, forgive me, I didn't know, I did not realize that.

01:07:10.760 --> 01:07:13.200
[Guest]: He's like, you tell me, how did you get your number?

01:07:13.200 --> 01:07:16.920
[Guest]: And I'm like, I mean, how did you get it, I said, sorry, he's like, no, no, I'm asking

01:07:16.920 --> 01:07:17.920
[Guest]: how did you get it?

01:07:17.920 --> 01:07:18.920
[Guest]: Explain it to me.

01:07:18.920 --> 01:07:21.560
[Guest]: How do you get a girl's number?

01:07:21.560 --> 01:07:27.480
[Guest]: I said, what do you want to do, you know, he's like, I want her number, but she's your

01:07:27.480 --> 01:07:28.480
[Guest]: girlfriend.

01:07:28.480 --> 01:07:32.560
[Guest]: And his actual words were, but don't tell her, she's my girlfriend.

01:07:32.560 --> 01:07:35.800
[Guest]: I'm like, what is going on in this college?

01:07:35.800 --> 01:07:39.960
[Guest]: So I said, well, I just asked her, man, you have to just be like polite and like, she

01:07:39.960 --> 01:07:40.960
[Guest]: gave it.

01:07:40.960 --> 01:07:42.480
[Guest]: He's like, explain it to me.

01:07:42.480 --> 01:07:46.480
[Guest]: And somehow during then, I mean, this was the first such incident.

01:07:46.480 --> 01:07:51.440
[Guest]: And from that point, for whatever it's for, whatever reasons, the Haryanvi kids who would

01:07:51.440 --> 01:07:56.160
[Guest]: not very well fit in with all the other kids from different states.

01:07:56.160 --> 01:08:00.240
[Guest]: And there was a lot of rivalry and I mean, you know, a lot of anger, a lot of fights

01:08:00.240 --> 01:08:02.480
[Guest]: that have happened in our college, etc.

01:08:02.480 --> 01:08:08.240
[Guest]: For whatever reasons, I got a little bit of respect because I, again, maybe polished or

01:08:08.240 --> 01:08:13.600
[Guest]: whatever in Polish, when I say again, not in a, in just the way that I would speak a

01:08:13.600 --> 01:08:19.640
[Guest]: certain way, I was like a, which was, which was this understanding of what, what it meant

01:08:19.640 --> 01:08:26.960
[Guest]: to be, what, what your Indian society needs you to be after a certain point of time.

01:08:26.960 --> 01:08:33.760
[Guest]: So I was a prototype of like, this is what happens after four years of engineering college.

01:08:33.760 --> 01:08:40.840
[Guest]: And somebody who is already knows English, already has, quote unquote, self confidence,

01:08:40.840 --> 01:08:45.920
[Guest]: already can talk to girls, already can like write, you know, so and, and for whatever

01:08:45.920 --> 01:08:48.680
[Guest]: it's worth, I was not an asshole, you know, and that was something that, you know, everybody

01:08:48.680 --> 01:08:53.320
[Guest]: found like a very unique thing about me, whereas other NRE kids typically were seem to be as

01:08:53.320 --> 01:08:54.320
[Guest]: assholes.

01:08:54.320 --> 01:08:58.640
[Guest]: I mean, no offense, but that's just how it was.

01:08:58.640 --> 01:09:04.720
[Guest]: And so suddenly, all the boys, Haryanvi boys kind of also gave me the liberty and the respect

01:09:04.720 --> 01:09:09.000
[Guest]: to kind of talk to them, whenever there was something that they were doing wrong, they

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:12.640
[Guest]: would come to me to ask me about like, you know, aise kaise karte hain, aise kaise karte

01:09:12.640 --> 01:09:13.640
[Guest]: hain, very generously.

01:09:13.640 --> 01:09:17.840
[Guest]: And I really like respect that, that, you know, there were people who would ask ki jana,

01:09:17.840 --> 01:09:21.000
[Guest]: ab mujhe ladki saath, I need to ask her out, how do I do it?

01:09:21.000 --> 01:09:24.640
[Guest]: And you know, and I'm just like, I've had one girlfriend before this, I'm not like a,

01:09:24.640 --> 01:09:28.600
[Guest]: I'm not hitch, you know, mujhe ithara bhi nahi bata, I'm right now, I was, you know,

01:09:28.600 --> 01:09:31.840
[Guest]: going through a heartbreak, theek hai, but whatever, I'm helping.

01:09:31.840 --> 01:09:35.960
[Guest]: On the other hand, whenever there was somebody who would be rude, obnoxious, inappropriate,

01:09:35.960 --> 01:09:44.600
[Guest]: which I saw a lot of, I saw so many young boys, just be filthy with girls.

01:09:44.600 --> 01:09:48.960
[Guest]: And in their heads, that's just how they thought.

01:09:48.960 --> 01:09:53.480
[Guest]: You know, you flirt, unko lagta tha, flirt karna hota hai ki ladki attitude rakhti hain

01:09:53.480 --> 01:09:56.800
[Guest]: na, to as a boy, what you need to do is you need to call and give them gaalis.

01:09:56.800 --> 01:10:00.480
[Guest]: To gaali deke na, to usko, apne aap jo na, wo bole ki usko samajh aata hai ki ladka bhi

01:10:00.480 --> 01:10:02.280
[Guest]: na, uske andar te se zyada attitude hai.

01:10:02.280 --> 01:10:06.680
[Guest]: Aur jab baat chal jayega ki you have more attitudes, wo pighal jayegi, and then she'll

01:10:06.680 --> 01:10:08.600
[Guest]: be like, okay, this is the guy I want.

01:10:08.600 --> 01:10:11.640
[Guest]: Because this is the guy who'll protect me, because he has more attitude than me.

01:10:11.640 --> 01:10:13.160
[Guest]: This is the way they used to think.

01:10:13.160 --> 01:10:16.320
[Guest]: Girls would change their phone numbers, they would find a new phone number, leak it, and

01:10:16.320 --> 01:10:20.080
[Guest]: then everybody would have, everybody would call in, everybody would send these insanely

01:10:20.080 --> 01:10:22.520
[Guest]: dirty messages, and I would watch this with horror.

01:10:22.520 --> 01:10:24.840
[Guest]: I'm like, how are you doing this, right?

01:10:24.840 --> 01:10:27.360
[Guest]: And again, none of this right now coming from a place where I didn't know what feminism

01:10:27.360 --> 01:10:28.360
[Guest]: is or whatever it is.

01:10:28.360 --> 01:10:30.360
[Guest]: Just, I thought it's just human decency, right?

01:10:30.360 --> 01:10:31.920
[Guest]: Like, don't be such an asshole.

01:10:31.920 --> 01:10:34.840
[Guest]: And I'd go up to, like, these kids.

01:10:34.840 --> 01:10:37.680
[Guest]: And again, I'm not just saying that they are only from Haryana, they're all kinds of places

01:10:37.680 --> 01:10:41.800
[Guest]: that people would become, who would giving me that respect of like, ki theek hai, tum

01:10:41.800 --> 01:10:42.800
[Guest]: mujhe bol sakte ho.

01:10:42.800 --> 01:10:49.360
[Guest]: I remember this one time where, like, this guy said, in, in a, in a truth or dare game,

01:10:49.360 --> 01:10:53.760
[Guest]: among a classroom, in a canteen, asked a girl to say, what is your bra size?

01:10:53.760 --> 01:10:55.080
[Guest]: And I was like, how?

01:10:55.080 --> 01:10:58.880
[Guest]: And I just got so, I was so irritated, I was like, shut up.

01:10:58.880 --> 01:11:00.280
[Guest]: That's not what you say.

01:11:00.280 --> 01:11:04.120
[Guest]: And then it became awkward and like, whatever, you know, and then later also, he didn't say

01:11:04.120 --> 01:11:05.120
[Guest]: anything to me at that time.

01:11:05.120 --> 01:11:08.600
[Guest]: Raat ka again, he came to me, he's a different guy, came to me in the night, he says, dekh

01:11:08.600 --> 01:11:10.720
[Guest]: mai teri aizad karta hu, tu jo bolega, main sununga.

01:11:10.720 --> 01:11:13.640
[Guest]: Tu mujhe samjhayega na, ki yeh nahi karna chahiye, main nahi karunga.

01:11:13.640 --> 01:11:17.360
[Unknown]: But agli baar, tu ne kiske saamne mujhe shut up bola na, toh wahin dhar doga tujhe.

01:11:17.360 --> 01:11:21.240
[Unknown]: I was like, but theek hai, chalo, sun toh liya na, aur kuch maara nahi.

01:11:21.240 --> 01:11:24.400
[Guest]: So I've come very close to getting beaten up by these guys, but just somehow just been

01:11:24.400 --> 01:11:25.400
[Guest]: let off.

01:11:25.400 --> 01:11:30.240
[Guest]: But I understood like there is, you know, and in that college is where I got the first

01:11:30.240 --> 01:11:36.680
[Guest]: sense of like, the deep, deep patriarchal conditioning that happens.

01:11:36.680 --> 01:11:40.120
[Guest]: And you know, again, they were not, these are not evil people, right?

01:11:40.120 --> 01:11:44.320
[Guest]: They were not, it's not that they were bad human beings.

01:11:44.320 --> 01:11:46.560
[Guest]: It's just that that's how they were conditioned.

01:11:46.560 --> 01:11:50.640
[Guest]: Most young boys that I've met at that time, from whichever part of the country, unfortunately

01:11:50.640 --> 01:11:55.000
[Guest]: had a certain idea of what women are and what women should be and, you know, what we should

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:57.440
[Guest]: be doing with them and how we should be thinking of them.

01:11:57.440 --> 01:12:01.880
[Guest]: And again, I'm not saying that I was not, as a, you know, young horny teenager, even

01:12:01.880 --> 01:12:04.080
[Guest]: I used to objectify girls as a teenager, etc.

01:12:04.080 --> 01:12:09.040
[Guest]: But at the same time, I was not like, I just felt like this was way too extreme, ki theek

01:12:09.040 --> 01:12:12.400
[Guest]: hai tum, you're thinking about them and talking about them with your best friend, like, oh,

01:12:12.400 --> 01:12:13.760
[Guest]: I like this girl and whatever.

01:12:13.760 --> 01:12:14.760
[Guest]: That's one thing.

01:12:14.760 --> 01:12:18.960
[Guest]: But like, you know, getting as part of a community, people used to watch porn together, yaar.

01:12:18.960 --> 01:12:24.120
[Guest]: That was the weirdest for me, like, poor community, 6 log, 10 log na saath mein aate na porn saath

01:12:24.120 --> 01:12:27.840
[Guest]: mein dekh rahe hain, ek kamadi ke andar hai, I'd just be like, kaise kar rahe ho tum, yeh

01:12:27.840 --> 01:12:28.840
[Guest]: kya chal raha hai?

01:12:28.840 --> 01:12:30.800
[Guest]: So I was just, I was an alien in that world.

01:12:30.800 --> 01:12:33.280
[Guest]: I would just be like, this is, this is weird.

01:12:33.280 --> 01:12:37.960
[Guest]: But I realized that there are certain gender dynamics, you know, and again, the understanding

01:12:37.960 --> 01:12:44.320
[Guest]: of privilege that I had, that clearly there is, you know, something that I seem to have

01:12:44.320 --> 01:12:46.760
[Guest]: an understanding of that others don't.

01:12:46.760 --> 01:12:54.480
[Guest]: And maybe, you know, I can try in whatever manner to help, you know, without looking

01:12:54.480 --> 01:12:59.240
[Guest]: down, without having judgment, without shaming anybody who thinks like this, just try to

01:12:59.240 --> 01:13:03.000
[Guest]: talk them, talk to them and help them understand what, why, what they're doing and why they're

01:13:03.000 --> 01:13:04.000
[Guest]: doing it is wrong.

01:13:04.000 --> 01:13:07.920
[Guest]: I again did not know what this is conditioning the society, yeh sab mujhe nahi pata tha.

01:13:07.920 --> 01:13:12.440
[Guest]: Just as a, you know, again, just as a, I would say a decent person, a decent human being

01:13:12.440 --> 01:13:19.000
[Guest]: who later when I realized was, had that, like empathy is also privilege, you know, I genuinely

01:13:19.000 --> 01:13:20.000
[Guest]: feel that.

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:26.880
[Guest]: I feel like, you know, having that awareness of, of, you are not born quote unquote, you

01:13:26.880 --> 01:13:34.880
[Guest]: know, with again, I, I, I'm using this word again and I, and I want to use it in those

01:13:34.880 --> 01:13:40.080
[Guest]: setting of those quotes, sophisticated, you know, that there's an idea that every, you

01:13:40.080 --> 01:13:45.040
[Guest]: know, parent has for their young Indian child that, you know, if you wear a certain kind

01:13:45.040 --> 01:13:49.440
[Guest]: of clothes, if you have a certain kind of a way of speaking, if you know English in

01:13:49.440 --> 01:13:55.480
[Guest]: a certain way, if you, you know, your hair is done in a certain way, if you, if the,

01:13:55.480 --> 01:14:02.020
[Guest]: that's what a sophisticated young Indian boy should be like, you know, and it was, and

01:14:02.020 --> 01:14:06.640
[Guest]: I started recognizing that this is where earlier I used to look at maybe other kids like that,

01:14:06.640 --> 01:14:10.600
[Guest]: that he is more sophisticated than me, now I understand that people are looking at me

01:14:10.600 --> 01:14:14.760
[Guest]: and saying that I am more than them, so where I was feeling misfit there, I was feeling

01:14:14.760 --> 01:14:19.440
[Guest]: misfit here too, but in a very different way, where I was fully aware of the class and caste

01:14:19.440 --> 01:14:23.560
[Guest]: privilege that I had without knowing these terms at that time, and that's where I think

01:14:23.560 --> 01:14:30.400
[Guest]: in many ways my, you know, understanding of gender really started from, and then, I mean,

01:14:30.400 --> 01:14:34.000
[Guest]: I started dating a girl over there and the kind of shit that, you know, we've gone through

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:39.640
[Guest]: in college, I can't get too much into it beyond the point again, because it is my wife's story,

01:14:39.640 --> 01:14:44.800
[Guest]: I don't want to, but we went through some really horrible times in college where, you

01:14:44.800 --> 01:14:51.480
[Guest]: know, there were rumors spread about us and whatever it is, just really nasty stuff, and

01:14:51.480 --> 01:14:56.560
[Guest]: I was just, I just couldn't understand why would, you know, why would society behave

01:14:56.560 --> 01:15:00.480
[Guest]: in this manner, you know, what have we done to any of you, like, where is this coming

01:15:00.480 --> 01:15:05.600
[Guest]: from, why would you say something so shameful and so hurtful about other people, you know,

01:15:05.600 --> 01:15:09.240
[Guest]: when it comes and break it down into, well, this is what a man does, this is what a woman

01:15:09.240 --> 01:15:13.520
[Guest]: does, so clearly there is something here, like, where is this, what is happening, so

01:15:13.520 --> 01:15:18.680
[Guest]: the culture only, I just kind of, so where I was fitting in from a lens of, you know,

01:15:18.680 --> 01:15:24.120
[Guest]: where I was finding myself at ease in a bunch of people who are definitely who I seemed

01:15:24.120 --> 01:15:28.440
[Guest]: closer to, in terms of like, if I would have never gone to the Middle East, these are the

01:15:28.440 --> 01:15:31.720
[Guest]: kind of kids I would have exactly been like, right, so I was a little bit more comfortable

01:15:31.720 --> 01:15:35.220
[Guest]: and at ease with my friends over there than I've ever been with anybody in the Middle

01:15:35.220 --> 01:15:36.220
[Guest]: East.

01:15:36.220 --> 01:15:40.960
[Guest]: At the same time, after a point of time, because of the cultural differences, you know, that

01:15:40.960 --> 01:15:44.000
[Guest]: because I'd spent that time there, I still started realizing there's a big vast difference

01:15:44.000 --> 01:15:48.640
[Guest]: in the way everybody's been conditioned, where my conditioning allowed me to have the privilege

01:15:48.640 --> 01:15:53.040
[Guest]: of looking at, you know, people beyond the lenses of gender and as human beings, and

01:15:53.040 --> 01:15:58.720
[Guest]: as stories, and versus as like, you know, this is a boy, this is a girl, this is what

01:15:58.720 --> 01:16:03.480
[Guest]: they do, you know, I just, with everybody else, there was a very clear divide, and in

01:16:03.480 --> 01:16:08.080
[Guest]: that divide, boys behaved in a certain way and girls behaved in a certain way, and it

01:16:08.080 --> 01:16:10.320
[Guest]: was, it was a divide.

01:16:10.320 --> 01:16:14.480
[Guest]: So I went through some really tough times, again, there's just some stuff that I'd rather

01:16:14.480 --> 01:16:19.920
[Guest]: not get into, but, you know, in college, and then when I got into Bombay, again, it was

01:16:19.920 --> 01:16:25.040
[Guest]: like a whole shift, Bombay, now, I've been in Kurukshetra for 4 years now, and if a girl

01:16:25.040 --> 01:16:29.440
[Guest]: is sitting at a place, where a guy comes and sits next to her, they'd be like, oh, that

01:16:29.440 --> 01:16:33.520
[Guest]: guy likes that girl, literally, you like her, you've sat in the same seat as she's at, like,

01:16:33.520 --> 01:16:38.280
[Guest]: what is this, what, what are you talking about, Mahima spoke about like the, the hostile

01:16:38.280 --> 01:16:42.800
[Guest]: time, you know, times, right, like, I used to feel so terrible about the fact that, you

01:16:42.800 --> 01:16:47.640
[Guest]: know, like, I get to be in that college, and at the very minimum, I mean, I didn't go to

01:16:47.640 --> 01:16:50.680
[Guest]: the library much, let me be honest, but you know, the fact that there are people who had

01:16:50.680 --> 01:16:54.600
[Guest]: access to the library throughout the night, you know, till 12 o'clock, and girls had to

01:16:54.600 --> 01:17:00.040
[Guest]: 5.30, 6 o'clock, go back to the, never had, like, you know, the liberty or the freedom

01:17:00.040 --> 01:17:06.240
[Guest]: to explore, you know, outside of just the X number of hours they were, you know, in

01:17:06.240 --> 01:17:10.320
[Guest]: college, and it was just so unfair, you know, the whole system I had to drop and I was also

01:17:10.320 --> 01:17:13.360
[Guest]: coming from a place, I like this girl, why do I have to drop her at 6 o'clock, I want

01:17:13.360 --> 01:17:15.320
[Guest]: to spend more time with her.

01:17:15.320 --> 01:17:20.120
[Guest]: But yeah, but and then I came to Bombay, and then suddenly, like my, I was in an HT, where

01:17:20.120 --> 01:17:24.720
[Guest]: I was one of two guys and in a, in a team where everybody else was a woman.

01:17:24.720 --> 01:17:30.040
[Guest]: And suddenly, like where I had been fighting a certain kind of patriarchal conditioning

01:17:30.040 --> 01:17:34.920
[Guest]: and misogyny and in the way that things were structured in Kurukshetra, it was the absolute

01:17:34.920 --> 01:17:36.000
[Guest]: opposite over here.

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:41.360
[Guest]: And then I had to, again, rewire and kind of be like, Acha, now I can't think like that.

01:17:41.360 --> 01:17:45.960
[Guest]: I need to think in a different way, again, I need to like, you know, be more comfortable,

01:17:45.960 --> 01:17:48.880
[Guest]: I was not comfortable for the longest time, I couldn't hug girls, it was such a it became

01:17:48.880 --> 01:17:53.720
[Guest]: such a big issue for me, like, it became so awkward, I just did not.

01:17:53.720 --> 01:17:57.000
[Guest]: I don't I just don't know, like people girls would come and hug every, you know, everyone

01:17:57.000 --> 01:18:01.320
[Guest]: in like, in Bombay, this is very cool, and your friends and doesn't matter, right.

01:18:01.320 --> 01:18:06.400
[Guest]: But I was just at freeze, I'd be like, wait, you know, someone's guilty, someone give me

01:18:06.400 --> 01:18:08.680
[Guest]: a kiss, I just be like, what the hell happened?

01:18:08.680 --> 01:18:12.600
[Guest]: Because four years of Kurukshetra conditioned me that deeply to like, look at it as like

01:18:12.600 --> 01:18:16.840
[Guest]: a problem, you know, and if you have your own girlfriend, you have your own partner,

01:18:16.840 --> 01:18:17.840
[Guest]: that's one thing.

01:18:17.840 --> 01:18:22.960
[Guest]: But the moment you are in a, you know, system of people, you have to have boundaries.

01:18:22.960 --> 01:18:27.120
[Guest]: So all of this really ultimately came down to two things.

01:18:27.120 --> 01:18:30.880
[Guest]: It's a long winded answer, but two things have happened.

01:18:30.880 --> 01:18:36.560
[Guest]: One is, as I said, and again, I think we might get deeper into it was mental health, you

01:18:36.560 --> 01:18:42.160
[Guest]: know, which is at 30, I got I was diagnosed with clinical anxiety.

01:18:42.160 --> 01:18:51.200
[Guest]: And a lot of my therapy ultimately ended up being about gender, you know, my till that

01:18:51.200 --> 01:18:56.200
[Guest]: point, I had never thought of my identity as a man ever.

01:18:56.200 --> 01:19:00.040
[Guest]: You should ask me what I said, I could have given you x number of answers, but the answer

01:19:00.040 --> 01:19:01.600
[Guest]: would never be a man.

01:19:01.600 --> 01:19:05.040
[Guest]: And in my in my therapy sessions, I realized that everything that had happened in my life,

01:19:05.040 --> 01:19:08.080
[Guest]: every decision that I had made was because I was a man.

01:19:08.080 --> 01:19:11.120
[Guest]: Every decision I'd made wasn't for no other reason.

01:19:11.120 --> 01:19:14.080
[Guest]: The reason that I had to go to engineering college was because I'm a man.

01:19:14.080 --> 01:19:20.720
[Guest]: The reason that I had to, you know, it was such a big fight with me and my parents, when

01:19:20.720 --> 01:19:27.200
[Guest]: I had to, you know, be when I had to take up something else outside of engineering when

01:19:27.200 --> 01:19:31.840
[Guest]: I had to take up Hindustan Times MTV, you know, my parents wouldn't understand because

01:19:31.840 --> 01:19:35.520
[Guest]: I was a man because they had a certain and I had to do MBA, I've studied, I've given

01:19:35.520 --> 01:19:40.800
[Guest]: CAT, I've given GMATS, you know, I used to get up at four o'clock every morning after

01:19:40.800 --> 01:19:46.320
[Guest]: point in time while I was studying, working at Hindustan Times to go to and to do mock

01:19:46.320 --> 01:19:47.320
[Guest]: tests and whatnot.

01:19:47.320 --> 01:19:49.040
[Guest]: Because I was just like, I don't know, I was in despair.

01:19:49.040 --> 01:19:50.040
[Guest]: I didn't know what else to do.

01:19:50.040 --> 01:19:51.680
[Guest]: I was like, I'll do my work.

01:19:51.680 --> 01:19:56.040
[Guest]: And in that work for that matter, just to tell you again, at 22, 23, I've interviewed

01:19:56.040 --> 01:20:01.280
[Guest]: everyone Shahrukh Khan, Salman Khan, Amitabh Bachchan, Aamir Khan, A. R. Rahman, you name

01:20:01.280 --> 01:20:03.880
[Guest]: it, all the big folks at 22, 23, I've done it.

01:20:03.880 --> 01:20:05.960
[Guest]: So I was outperforming everywhere.

01:20:05.960 --> 01:20:06.960
[Guest]: But there was never enough.

01:20:06.960 --> 01:20:07.960
[Guest]: It was never enough.

01:20:07.960 --> 01:20:14.240
[Guest]: It was always about the fact that if you do MBA, you'll get this much money.

01:20:14.240 --> 01:20:18.400
[Guest]: So I realized that so much, even though now I was, I'd come to Yashraj and I'd got

01:20:18.400 --> 01:20:24.240
[Guest]: a bunch of, you know, touchwood success at YRF, where I was in a very comfortable position.

01:20:24.240 --> 01:20:29.040
[Guest]: I'd gotten everything that, you know, there's a middle class checklist, you know, you shouldn't

01:20:29.040 --> 01:20:32.560
[Guest]: have a designation, you shouldn't have a cabin, you know, you shouldn't have so much money

01:20:32.560 --> 01:20:34.120
[Guest]: in the bank, you shouldn't have a car, etc.

01:20:34.120 --> 01:20:36.240
[Guest]: I'd got all of that and that was by 30.

01:20:36.240 --> 01:20:42.640
[Guest]: And then when I reached there, the question then came to be like, now I've done it.

01:20:42.640 --> 01:20:44.920
[Guest]: Now what?

01:20:44.920 --> 01:20:46.960
[Guest]: And I couldn't, I didn't have an answer.

01:20:46.960 --> 01:20:50.480
[Guest]: Because what happens when you hit those milestones that you've been trying to hit all your life?

01:20:50.480 --> 01:20:51.480
[Guest]: There is no answer.

01:20:51.480 --> 01:20:54.320
[Guest]: There are, there's just more milestones to go to.

01:20:54.320 --> 01:20:56.440
[Guest]: And then I was just like, is that it?

01:20:56.440 --> 01:21:00.600
[Guest]: There's this quote, I think, I don't know who it is by, right, like, I hope, say it's

01:21:00.600 --> 01:21:04.720
[Guest]: by Jim Carrey that, I don't know if it's by him, but that I hope everyone gets the fame

01:21:04.720 --> 01:21:08.560
[Guest]: and money, all the fame and money that they want so that they know it's not the answer,

01:21:08.560 --> 01:21:09.560
[Guest]: you know.

01:21:09.560 --> 01:21:14.240
[Guest]: So I did get whatever, you know, level of what I wanted, the middle class checklist.

01:21:14.240 --> 01:21:17.600
[Guest]: And then I realized that I'm unhappy still.

01:21:17.600 --> 01:21:18.600
[Guest]: I'm not happy.

01:21:18.600 --> 01:21:24.200
[Guest]: In fact, my unhappiness, after all the legitimate success that I was seeing with my work at

01:21:24.200 --> 01:21:30.520
[Guest]: Yash Raj, I was just, I felt like I was in a machine, in a simulation where I'm every

01:21:30.520 --> 01:21:35.880
[Guest]: morning getting up, going to work, you know, in this traffic, you know, sitting in my desk,

01:21:35.880 --> 01:21:41.240
[Guest]: working on something that somebody else, a corporation, even if it was Yash Raj films

01:21:41.240 --> 01:21:44.200
[Guest]: that I have the best time working there, I was still working on something that somebody

01:21:44.200 --> 01:21:45.440
[Guest]: else might want from me.

01:21:45.440 --> 01:21:48.560
[Guest]: There is, I was doing it in the service of getting somebody else a certain amount of

01:21:48.560 --> 01:21:52.200
[Guest]: money for an ambition that somebody else may have had somewhere.

01:21:52.200 --> 01:21:53.600
[Guest]: What was I doing for myself?

01:21:53.600 --> 01:21:54.600
[Guest]: What was I doing?

01:21:54.600 --> 01:21:58.960
[Guest]: You know, did I even know what myself is?

01:21:58.960 --> 01:22:05.200
[Guest]: You know, do I even know, like, if I didn't have, if I didn't just run from one milestone

01:22:05.200 --> 01:22:11.640
[Guest]: to another, if I didn't just go from one day to the next without ever having, I don't think

01:22:11.640 --> 01:22:17.160
[Guest]: Amit in my entire life, I have quote unquote chilled on a weekend in my entire life so

01:22:17.160 --> 01:22:18.160
[Guest]: far.

01:22:18.160 --> 01:22:20.440
[Guest]: I used to fill my Sundays and Saturdays up.

01:22:20.440 --> 01:22:24.840
[Guest]: I'd go teach on the weekends, you know, in Jai Hind, in Churchgate, you know, because

01:22:24.840 --> 01:22:29.160
[Guest]: I was like, weekends are for, you know, I mean, I have time, what am I going to do with

01:22:29.160 --> 01:22:30.160
[Guest]: this time?

01:22:30.160 --> 01:22:31.160
[Guest]: I need to fill it up with more work.

01:22:31.160 --> 01:22:34.520
[Guest]: I was at one point when I was working at Yash Raj, I was writing an open magazine, I was

01:22:34.520 --> 01:22:38.280
[Guest]: writing a Sunday Guardian, I was teaching at Jai Hind, I was hosting a show from Film

01:22:38.280 --> 01:22:43.720
[Guest]: Companion, I was programming from Mumbai Film Festival, I was writing something for Scholastic

01:22:43.720 --> 01:22:48.160
[Guest]: every year, 80 things I was doing and still I continue doing even though now I have a

01:22:48.160 --> 01:22:52.720
[Guest]: better sense of it, but it's so hard, I'm scaling back now Sundays I don't work at all,

01:22:52.720 --> 01:22:58.120
[Guest]: but it's so hard, I still get anxiety on Sundays because I don't know, you know, I feel like

01:22:58.120 --> 01:23:02.040
[Guest]: am I, what am I doing in that time, I need to make it productive, productivity has to

01:23:02.040 --> 01:23:06.200
[Guest]: be the most important thing for me, you know, why, why can't I just relax?

01:23:06.200 --> 01:23:10.080
[Guest]: I realized every one of these things came down to being a man, you know, every one of

01:23:10.080 --> 01:23:14.360
[Guest]: these things came down to gender and that just really frustrated me because I was like,

01:23:14.360 --> 01:23:20.120
[Guest]: I just, because the one thing that I didn't want to be was a man because of my father

01:23:20.120 --> 01:23:26.400
[Guest]: and you know, again, I'd grown up all these years angry at him because he was quote-unquote

01:23:26.400 --> 01:23:31.680
[Guest]: a man who was, you know, not a good, who's not a father, who was not a husband, who's

01:23:31.680 --> 01:23:36.040
[Guest]: not a, was just a man, just earning for his and just constantly and I was doing the same

01:23:36.040 --> 01:23:37.040
[Guest]: thing.

01:23:37.040 --> 01:23:43.600
[Guest]: When I was making my first show, I remember like, I, for two years, I did not speak to

01:23:43.600 --> 01:23:44.600
[Guest]: my friends.

01:23:44.600 --> 01:23:46.360
[Guest]: I did not spend time with my family.

01:23:46.360 --> 01:23:51.520
[Guest]: You know, my brother and I stopped talking because I was just so, it was like, if the

01:23:51.520 --> 01:23:53.480
[Guest]: show fails, where will I land?

01:23:53.480 --> 01:23:54.480
[Guest]: What will my life be?

01:23:54.480 --> 01:23:58.680
[Guest]: It had become such a big thing that this cannot fail and it failed very spectacularly, which

01:23:58.680 --> 01:24:02.560
[Guest]: was again, and I realized much later that what I went through after that a year after

01:24:02.560 --> 01:24:03.560
[Guest]: that was also anxiety.

01:24:03.560 --> 01:24:05.080
[Guest]: I just didn't have the terms for it.

01:24:05.080 --> 01:24:08.980
[Guest]: But at 30, when I started going through anxiety, when I was doing well, which was the next

01:24:08.980 --> 01:24:13.640
[Guest]: new thing, right, like I, my understanding of mental health was that when you are going

01:24:13.640 --> 01:24:17.960
[Guest]: through, it happens when you're going through a low phase, I was going through the best,

01:24:17.960 --> 01:24:24.400
[Guest]: best phase of my entire life and I was unhappy and I was empty and I was sad and I just,

01:24:24.400 --> 01:24:27.280
[Guest]: and I was anxious as I used to have panic attacks.

01:24:27.280 --> 01:24:35.960
[Guest]: I used to, you know, I got the opportunity like the, to go for, I mean, started then

01:24:35.960 --> 01:24:40.120
[Guest]: there was, there's a event called goalkeepers that the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation

01:24:40.120 --> 01:24:42.120
[Guest]: hosts in New York in 2017.

01:24:42.120 --> 01:24:46.280
[Guest]: I got the opportunity to go as an India delegate, they call 300 emerging leaders from across

01:24:46.280 --> 01:24:47.280
[Guest]: the world.

01:24:47.280 --> 01:24:51.720
[Guest]: In that first year, Barack Obama was the keynote speaker, Justin Trudeau was there, Malala

01:24:51.720 --> 01:24:52.720
[Guest]: was there.

01:24:52.720 --> 01:24:53.720
[Guest]: It was insane.

01:24:53.720 --> 01:24:57.080
[Guest]: I was invited as a gathering of that people as, as far as you and I are sitting, I was

01:24:57.080 --> 01:25:03.600
[Guest]: that far, you know, just a little further from Barack Obama and, and I had so much anxiety.

01:25:03.600 --> 01:25:07.800
[Guest]: I was, I was shaking every day, I couldn't wake up in the mornings because I was like,

01:25:07.800 --> 01:25:10.360
[Guest]: they will find out that I don't know shit.

01:25:10.360 --> 01:25:15.840
[Guest]: They will find out that, you know, I'm an, you know, I'm, I'm not as, I don't deserve

01:25:15.840 --> 01:25:17.000
[Guest]: to be here.

01:25:17.000 --> 01:25:21.720
[Guest]: I had, I had to go to, I had to go to therapy like three times a week in the week that I

01:25:21.720 --> 01:25:24.440
[Guest]: was going to, I would have anxiety about everything.

01:25:24.440 --> 01:25:29.280
[Guest]: I remember the day this event was happening, I was in New York for the second, I mean,

01:25:29.280 --> 01:25:34.120
[Guest]: the first time I'd done it with my brother, with the second time ever, and I was, I was

01:25:34.120 --> 01:25:38.400
[Guest]: in a hotel and I was, and I couldn't get up in the morning.

01:25:38.400 --> 01:25:42.760
[Guest]: I just, I had such a massive, the first time I realized that this is what a panic attack,

01:25:42.760 --> 01:25:45.480
[Guest]: I mean, later much later I realized, I thought I was having a heart attack.

01:25:45.480 --> 01:25:47.400
[Guest]: I was in the bed, I couldn't get up.

01:25:47.400 --> 01:25:50.720
[Guest]: My heart was, it, it was all over.

01:25:50.720 --> 01:25:54.440
[Guest]: I just, I thought this is it, this is, I'm, this is it for me.

01:25:54.440 --> 01:25:55.440
[Guest]: Like it was so bad.

01:25:55.440 --> 01:26:00.880
[Guest]: And my first thoughts always just come down to, I wish I'd told my mother my e-banking

01:26:00.880 --> 01:26:03.960
[Unknown]: passwords as if there was a lot of money there, there's nothing there.

01:26:03.960 --> 01:26:06.560
[Guest]: But those are the thoughts that used to come to my, my head.

01:26:06.560 --> 01:26:08.320
[Guest]: But it was just, I was like, this is it for me.

01:26:08.320 --> 01:26:10.560
[Guest]: I'm going to die in a hotel room in New York.

01:26:10.560 --> 01:26:14.200
[Guest]: You know, it's a nice room, but like, I'm going to die here.

01:26:14.200 --> 01:26:19.720
[Guest]: And then somehow after like 15, 20 minutes of trying to deal with it, I caught up and

01:26:19.720 --> 01:26:23.400
[Guest]: then it's like, okay, I'm still alive somehow, went there.

01:26:23.400 --> 01:26:29.160
[Guest]: But like the questions that started at that time was just like, what is the point of this?

01:26:29.160 --> 01:26:30.980
[Guest]: Why am I doing this?

01:26:30.980 --> 01:26:32.960
[Guest]: Why does any of this matter?

01:26:32.960 --> 01:26:35.920
[Guest]: And these are larger existential questions that I think everyone at some point goes through

01:26:35.920 --> 01:26:42.520
[Guest]: for, but for me, it really came down to the fact that my entire life was just me leading

01:26:42.520 --> 01:26:46.600
[Guest]: a story that was given to me by somebody else that was given to me by society, not even

01:26:46.600 --> 01:26:49.000
[Guest]: my parents and society and parents were given to a society, right?

01:26:49.000 --> 01:26:56.280
[Guest]: So I was just following the society's narrative of what a life should be like.

01:26:56.280 --> 01:27:01.080
[Guest]: And every fight that I had, every, every day I was angry, my relationship with my father,

01:27:01.080 --> 01:27:05.760
[Guest]: my relationship with my work, my relationship with my mother, my relationship with my wife,

01:27:05.760 --> 01:27:11.560
[Guest]: everything, every single thing was, you know, colored with patriarchy.

01:27:11.560 --> 01:27:15.360
[Guest]: And I tried my best to be the best possible husband to my wife.

01:27:15.360 --> 01:27:19.480
[Guest]: I was like, you know, so if the only time I started having weekends or caring was in

01:27:19.480 --> 01:27:26.000
[Guest]: Yashraj, people were like, you're the only person in Bollywood who doesn't pick up phones

01:27:26.000 --> 01:27:27.000
[Guest]: on Saturdays and Sundays.

01:27:27.000 --> 01:27:29.840
[Guest]: I was like, I'm married, I'm with my wife, I don't want to do it.

01:27:29.840 --> 01:27:31.640
[Guest]: Because I wanted to be the opposite of my father.

01:27:31.640 --> 01:27:34.260
[Guest]: So I was just like, I'm not going to be him.

01:27:34.260 --> 01:27:42.200
[Guest]: So I'm going to constantly just give myself that, you know, that space to be a good husband.

