01:56:54.600 --> 01:56:56.800
[Guest]: He's got tons of girls after him.

01:56:56.800 --> 01:57:00.720
[Guest]: He's, he might be going after one girl, but ultimately his every film is a coming of age

01:57:00.720 --> 01:57:05.480
[Guest]: film where he's trying to come to terms with who he is and trying to find out who he is.

01:57:05.480 --> 01:57:08.200
[Guest]: At the end of the film, whether it is through a girl, whether it is through a, you know,

01:57:08.200 --> 01:57:12.360
[Guest]: a job, whether it is through any other thing, whether it's a drama or whatever, he, he has

01:57:12.360 --> 01:57:14.140
[Guest]: a revelation at the end of it.

01:57:14.140 --> 01:57:16.040
[Guest]: And then he realizes this is who I am.

01:57:16.040 --> 01:57:20.240
[Guest]: I'm not, you know, I'm not a child anymore.

01:57:20.240 --> 01:57:21.240
[Guest]: I'm a man.

01:57:21.240 --> 01:57:24.120
[Guest]: And you know, and that process through that process, whether it's in Yeh Jawani, Yeh

01:57:24.120 --> 01:57:30.240
[Guest]: Diwani, wherever you see it, ultimately, I don't want to fall, I want to fly.

01:57:30.240 --> 01:57:33.760
[Guest]: I want to walk, I want to run, I don't want to fall.

01:57:33.760 --> 01:57:38.680
[Guest]: That's the whole generation of young men where Ranbir Kapoor came in and you had another

01:57:38.680 --> 01:57:39.680
[Guest]: hero.

01:57:39.680 --> 01:57:43.360
[Guest]: He was called Sid and Sid is now Ranbir Kapoor, right?

01:57:43.360 --> 01:57:48.560
[Guest]: This is that for three decades of cinema, literally as a character.

01:57:48.560 --> 01:57:53.000
[Guest]: And it's a man, that character is a man and he represents what men at that time are going

01:57:53.000 --> 01:57:54.000
[Guest]: through.

01:57:54.000 --> 01:57:57.400
