01:58:04.320 --> 01:58:07.560
[Guest]: Now you start caring about society around you because now you have found all of these

01:58:07.560 --> 01:58:08.560
[Guest]: four things.

01:58:08.560 --> 01:58:10.840
[Guest]: You also realize like thinking about yourself is important.

01:58:10.840 --> 01:58:12.320
[Guest]: Self-introspection is important.

01:58:12.320 --> 01:58:15.880
[Guest]: You know, being quote unquote with Ranbir Kapoor, being a fuckboy is also important.

01:58:15.880 --> 01:58:18.840
[Guest]: Then what, what really happens in life, then you maybe start looking at society.

01:58:18.840 --> 01:58:23.120
[Guest]: So Rajkumar, Ayushman, they have started like their own, you know, journeys of like showing

01:58:23.120 --> 01:58:26.280
[Guest]: the world a prism of, you know, here's the issues with society.

01:58:26.280 --> 01:58:28.440
[Guest]: You should care about it, etc, etc.

01:58:28.440 --> 01:58:34.280
[Guest]: Here at this point, also the female led film, as I said, started coming in as well.

01:58:34.280 --> 01:58:37.480
[Guest]: And you know why it really happened when you kind of go into the history as someone who's

01:58:37.480 --> 01:58:39.760
[Guest]: again worked in Bollywood for a bit.

01:58:39.760 --> 01:58:43.360
[Guest]: The history of female led films in India is that these are the, these are the films that

01:58:43.360 --> 01:58:45.080
[Guest]: men refuse to do.

01:58:45.080 --> 01:58:48.720
[Guest]: Most of these films were written for men and then men were like, this is too small.

01:58:48.720 --> 01:58:50.240
[Guest]: I'm not looking like a hero in this.

01:58:50.240 --> 01:58:53.440
[Guest]: I'm not a big, you know, I don't have much of an action scene.

01:58:53.440 --> 01:58:55.160
[Guest]: I don't think my arc is great.

01:58:55.160 --> 01:58:58.040
[Guest]: So then the directors and producers would be like, okay, what are you doing?

01:58:58.040 --> 01:59:03.120
[Guest]: So then you have to, you rewrite it and say, what if it was a woman?

01:59:03.120 --> 01:59:08.920
[Guest]: Examples, example, I mean, NH7 as an example, you know, again, I'm not, I'm not referring

01:59:08.920 --> 01:59:14.400
[Guest]: to this film as a very specific film about which would have happened here, but the general

01:59:14.400 --> 01:59:21.920
[Guest]: trend, you know, I mean, there are so many films that, you know, I also know that have

01:59:21.920 --> 01:59:25.640
[Guest]: changed from being, and I can't, because I was at Yansradha, I can't name them.

01:59:25.640 --> 01:59:27.200
[Amit Varma]: Bollywood people won't listen to it.

