02:01:00.880 --> 02:01:03.920
[Guest]: And in fact, and it's like a, it's a trial by fire.

02:01:03.920 --> 02:01:08.000
[Guest]: It's almost a coming of age for every Akshay Kumar film ki andar, Kiara Advani aagi for

02:01:08.000 --> 02:01:10.400
[Guest]: five scenes, then you know, that's when you get noticed.

02:01:10.400 --> 02:01:13.120
[Guest]: And then you can maybe someday lead your own film.

02:01:13.120 --> 02:01:17.160
[Guest]: That's the way people get to know you when you are opposite, or this is the way unfortunately

02:01:17.160 --> 02:01:18.740
[Guest]: things are structured, right?

02:01:18.740 --> 02:01:24.040
[Guest]: But when you see a female, a film which has a big female star, you have a Deepika, you

02:01:24.040 --> 02:01:30.440
[Guest]: know, in Chhapaak, you have a, you name it, you name it, you have Anushka in NH7, in NH40,

02:01:30.440 --> 02:01:32.360
[Guest]: I forget what the title was.

02:01:32.360 --> 02:01:38.720
[Guest]: You have Bhumi's films, Tapsee's films, you know, Rocket, Rashmi, any of these films,

02:01:38.720 --> 02:01:43.920
[Guest]: the male actors are always going to be folks who are either from a different industry,

02:01:43.920 --> 02:01:45.520
[Guest]: because they're not as big in Bollywood cinema.

02:01:45.520 --> 02:01:51.640
[Guest]: So they're okay with coming in like Punjabi cinema, I work in South, so I'm happy Dulukar

02:01:51.640 --> 02:01:52.640
[Guest]: Salman will come in.

