[Guest]: I reached out to like, anybody, you know, I used to blog a lot at that time on a website

03:18:41.560 --> 03:18:43.760
[Guest]: called on a forum called Zanga.

03:18:43.760 --> 03:18:49.040
[Guest]: So Zanga pe na logon ko, do you know anybody like, you know, in Bombay who would want to,

03:18:49.040 --> 03:18:51.440
[Guest]: you know, hire me and here's my resume or whatever.

03:18:51.440 --> 03:18:54.120
[Guest]: And my resume was like a lot of writing, of course, engineering college student, but a

03:18:54.120 --> 03:18:55.120
[Guest]: lot of writing that I'd done.

03:18:55.120 --> 03:18:59.280
[Guest]: I'd also started writing for Jam, which I think again is a rite of passage for most

03:18:59.280 --> 03:19:05.600
[Guest]: people at that time, you know, so, and kahi na kahi after like hundreds of attempts and

03:19:05.600 --> 03:19:08.240
[Guest]: hundreds of people, do you know, do you have a cousin in Bombay?

03:19:08.240 --> 03:19:11.360
[Guest]: Do you have somebody who knows somebody, etc, etc.

03:19:11.360 --> 03:19:15.200
[Guest]: Itne emails bheje maine, puri list mein, I remember like sabko, jiten logon jana tha

03:19:15.200 --> 03:19:20.840
[Guest]: ki Bombay kuch ko jante ho, media ke andar, I tried in NDTV, I tried in MTV, I tried everywhere.

03:19:20.840 --> 03:19:25.520
[Guest]: And then some, one of my junior's sister was working in Hindustan Times.

03:19:25.520 --> 03:19:31.520
[Guest]: She passed on my resume to Khalid Muhammad, who was the editor at HD Cafe.

03:19:31.520 --> 03:19:35.920
[Guest]: And yeah, I got a call and said, you know, very interesting CV, you guys want, you want

03:19:35.920 --> 03:19:36.920
[Guest]: to come over to Bombay?

03:19:36.920 --> 03:19:37.920
[Guest]: Can you come tomorrow for an interview?

03:19:37.920 --> 03:19:38.920
[Guest]: I was like, I'm in Karnal.

03:19:38.920 --> 03:19:39.920
[Guest]: So sure.

03:19:39.920 --> 03:19:40.920
[Guest]: Immediately, shyaam ko maine, subhe aagle din flight pagdi, Bombay mein mohacha, I'd

03:19:40.920 --> 03:19:41.920
[Guest]: add a folder of all the articles that I'd done.

03:19:41.920 --> 03:19:42.920
[Guest]: So it's like, what all have you done?

03:19:42.920 --> 03:19:43.920
[Guest]: I was like, yeh lo mera folder.

03:19:43.920 --> 03:19:56.440
[Guest]: So it was young times, you know, this, that, etc.

03:19:56.440 --> 03:19:59.640
[Guest]: So he's like, okay, great, you seem to be like young and smart, etc.

03:19:59.640 --> 03:20:00.640
[Guest]: This is what we can pay you.

03:20:00.640 --> 03:20:01.640
[Guest]: Yeah, you want to join?

03:20:01.640 --> 03:20:04.960
[Guest]: I said, oh yeah, so easily.

03:20:04.960 --> 03:20:08.400
[Guest]: And yeah, I never had to intern for whatever it's worth.

03:20:08.400 --> 03:20:10.920
[Guest]: And next day, I joined HD.

03:20:10.920 --> 03:20:14.640
[Guest]: And I mean, they told me literally that giving me some, you know, one week ka time diya tha,

03:20:14.640 --> 03:20:15.640
[Guest]: the one week I'd taken.

03:20:15.640 --> 03:20:21.320
[Guest]: Next day, I went back, came back a week later, 2008 July and joined HD.

03:20:21.320 --> 03:20:27.040
[Guest]: But it is, it is, it is through somebody else that I realized that this should be, this

03:20:27.040 --> 03:20:28.920
[Guest]: is what I should be doing.

03:20:28.920 --> 03:20:30.640
[Guest]: But and I had asked my mother for that.

03:20:30.640 --> 03:20:34.320
[Guest]: I mean, I didn't tell my mother, you know, at that time that I'm going to be applying

03:20:34.320 --> 03:20:35.320
[Guest]: to other places.

03:20:35.320 --> 03:20:36.560
[Guest]: I said, job mili viye hai.

03:20:36.560 --> 03:20:40.440
[Guest]: And then when I got this job, then I said, listen, so I have these two jobs, but I also

03:20:40.440 --> 03:20:42.560
[Guest]: have Hindustan Times now.

03:20:42.560 --> 03:20:46.440
[Guest]: And it's since it's HD, you know, and I'd also gotten jobs in two other, I'd got a job

03:20:46.440 --> 03:20:51.640
[Guest]: in OML, I'd got a job in a PR agency called Pink Relations, I remember.

03:20:51.640 --> 03:20:55.200
[Guest]: And so I'd got three jobs, and then I had to choose now, OML was paying me a little

03:20:55.200 --> 03:20:56.200
[Guest]: bit more than HD.

03:20:56.200 --> 03:20:58.080
[Guest]: Pink Relations was also paying me a little bit more.

03:20:58.080 --> 03:20:59.080
[Guest]: But HD was HD.

03:20:59.080 --> 03:21:03.000
[Guest]: So I was like, I mean, I can't now, Khalid Mohammed was somebody again, I read his newspaper,

03:21:03.000 --> 03:21:04.000
[Guest]: you know, reviews.

03:21:04.000 --> 03:21:06.840
[Guest]: I was like, if he's going to be my boss, I mean, I want to do this.

03:21:06.840 --> 03:21:12.640
[Guest]: Yeah, I came to Bombay, and you know, it's, and it's taken me until from that time on.

03:21:12.640 --> 03:21:16.760
[Guest]: But I think that's the first thing where again, an external circumstance and the second part

03:21:16.760 --> 03:21:20.320
[Guest]: would be my teaching.

03:21:20.320 --> 03:21:27.440
[Guest]: Hearing the stories of my students, you know, made me recognize that I need to introspect

03:21:27.440 --> 03:21:29.800
[Guest]: deeper into what is my own.

03:21:29.800 --> 03:21:37.920
[Guest]: Of course, anxiety and therapy were the big, ultimate points of transition in me recognizing

03:21:37.920 --> 03:21:43.560
[Guest]: became like Imtiaz Ali movie character, I took a sabbatical after, you know, so one

03:21:43.560 --> 03:21:46.760
[Guest]: of the things in therapy that after this whole conversation that I had, where she told me

03:21:46.760 --> 03:21:51.320
[Guest]: like, I had to figure out what do I want to do after I came back from goalkeepers from

03:21:51.320 --> 03:21:54.680
[Guest]: after that panic attack, I just came back and I decided that I realized what I want

03:21:54.680 --> 03:21:56.680
[Guest]: to do in life.

03:21:56.680 --> 03:21:57.960
[Guest]: I first want to quit.

03:21:57.960 --> 03:22:01.960
[Guest]: I don't think I can do my job, you know, and I need to give myself time.

03:22:01.960 --> 03:22:05.160
[Guest]: I need to take time to find out what is my story.

03:22:05.160 --> 03:22:11.720
[Guest]: And I and I and I decided to just and I told this, I remember I told this to my therapist,

03:22:11.720 --> 03:22:16.880
[Guest]: I was like, I decided I'm going to quit YRF and she's like, that's not what I told you.

03:22:16.880 --> 03:22:17.880
[Guest]: I told you to introspect.

03:22:17.880 --> 03:22:19.240
[Guest]: I didn't tell you to quit your job.

03:22:19.240 --> 03:22:20.440
[Guest]: I was like, no, no, I'm quitting.

03:22:20.440 --> 03:22:21.440
[Guest]: How can you quit YRF?

03:22:21.440 --> 03:22:22.440
[Guest]: She was like shocked.

03:22:22.440 --> 03:22:26.360
[Guest]: My parents, everybody was like, you are doing really well at YRF, don't quit.

03:22:26.360 --> 03:22:32.040
[Guest]: And and I was just but I was sure that I needed to give myself some time to figure out what

03:22:32.040 --> 03:22:33.040
[Guest]: is my story.

03:22:33.040 --> 03:22:36.920
[Guest]: And in those six and I took and I quit and I ultimately they were very kind, YRF was

03:22:36.920 --> 03:22:37.920
[Guest]: super kind.

03:22:37.920 --> 03:22:43.680
[Guest]: They've always been so kind to me, but they said like, you know, you take to you instead

03:22:43.680 --> 03:22:46.720
[Guest]: of like quitting, just take three months.

03:22:46.720 --> 03:22:49.360
[Guest]: And after three months, you tell us, do you want to continue or don't want to continue?

03:22:49.360 --> 03:22:50.360
[Guest]: That's fine.

03:22:50.360 --> 03:22:54.080
[Guest]: So after two months only, I knew that I didn't want to continue, but I so I kind of scrubbed

03:22:54.080 --> 03:23:02.480
[Guest]: off everything, left everything, left my teaching, left film companion, left YRF, left everything,

03:23:02.480 --> 03:23:08.080
[Guest]: switched off my phone, went to Bahrain, you know, with my parents for a few months.

03:23:08.080 --> 03:23:12.760
[Guest]: And to just and then I traveled a little bit, I kind of put a post online.

03:23:12.760 --> 03:23:17.920
[Guest]: And that's where I think even the Yuva's idea really started.

03:23:17.920 --> 03:23:22.280
[Guest]: I put a post online where I just told, you know, that I want to, I have quit my job.

03:23:22.280 --> 03:23:23.280
[Guest]: I have some time.

03:23:23.280 --> 03:23:24.600
[Guest]: I want to meet students across the country.

03:23:24.600 --> 03:23:26.800
[Guest]: If you are in a college in somewhere, please call me.

03:23:26.800 --> 03:23:28.040
[Guest]: I'd love to come over.

03:23:28.040 --> 03:23:32.800
[Guest]: So college in Indore called me, a college in Bangalore called me, a college in Bhubaneshwar

03:23:32.800 --> 03:23:34.320
[Guest]: called me.

03:23:34.320 --> 03:23:38.800
[Guest]: And I just went in all these different places and just met students for two to three days

03:23:38.800 --> 03:23:40.320
[Guest]: and speaking to them.

03:23:40.320 --> 03:23:43.760
[Guest]: And after all the work, I mean, all my teaching, and I know I've not spoken much about it,

03:23:43.760 --> 03:23:48.760
[Guest]: but teaching was the most transformative thing that has happened to me.

03:23:48.760 --> 03:23:55.440
[Guest]: You know, it is, yeah, because I think I entered teaching.

03:23:55.440 --> 03:24:00.000
[Guest]: I entered teaching with this idea with like that I am going to change people's lives,

03:24:00.000 --> 03:24:03.320
[Guest]: you know, and the reason for that was also because of my time at NID Kurukshetra.

03:24:03.320 --> 03:24:07.040
[Guest]: After a point of time when I had a full sense of my privilege, I just wanted to, for whatever

03:24:07.040 --> 03:24:10.120
[Guest]: it's worth, I just wanted to do whatever I can to give back.

03:24:10.120 --> 03:24:13.320
[Guest]: When I got a job, again, I'll tell you privilege ka kaise realization ho, when I got my job

